LogFile.FinalText: In many private homes you will find a pet and most people prefer a dog or a cat. So far, the soft puppy beats the cute kitty in the race of becoming Denmark's most popular pet. While the dog's loyalty explains its popularity, most cat owners love the cat's independence. Whereas the cat owner generally thinks that a dog is too independent and dirty, many dog owners consider cats to be lazy and impersonal. Many pet owners choose a pet which reflects their own personality. When a big strong man buys a big strong dog, the dog's characteristics reinforce the dog owner's ego. On the contrary, the feminine woman often prefers the beautiful and elegant cat. The dog and the cat normally get along just fine if they are used to each other's company. Often, the dog owner and the cat owner find it more difficult to get along.
